<subSubSection id="D554F30297F8CF212D6302B898DB518B" pageNumber="291" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="7785C8CB42F36C6C6BDDF39EB68CDBAA" pageNumber="291">
Although 
<normalizedToken id="FD95346C354A4749543904071E7B6614" originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis id="3179BF4E08A0D9A27CDE79D2A2DB8220" italics="true" pageNumber="291">Lejeunia</emphasis>
, n.s., 75: 196. 1975) stated &quot;Type: 
<normalizedToken id="FF1B15D5A3E9F03C71E8D8586797A54C" originalValue="…LINN”">...LINN&quot;</normalizedToken>
, this is not accepted as a formal typification, for the reasons explained by Cafferty &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis id="E230A99D3308282FE10C26163B32E1A6" italics="true" pageNumber="291">Taxon</emphasis>
49: 240. 2000). Romero Zarco (in 
<emphasis id="ECBD205F2A084AB95AE4728C45E57CBB" italics="true" pageNumber="291">Lagascalia</emphasis>
14: 122. 1986) subsequently chose 1211.15 (LINN) as 
<typeStatus id="B5CAE816F65A08AC86AA17D460CDFE01">lectotype</typeStatus>
but 
<normalizedToken id="6FF0144C909D82B421EC74F8265A6AA4" originalValue="Clayton’s">Clayton's</normalizedToken>
choice has priority. See 
<normalizedToken id="13CB19718329529D9636B4E5E0957A9C" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="CFFDD44955664F0685C0EC2A87EE73E0" originalValue="González">Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis id="E152E2FB4A8EAF5ED237EC832C949840" italics="true" pageNumber="291">Anales Jard. Bot. Madrid</emphasis>
51: 313. 1993), who discusses various aspects of the typification of this name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
